reviews.review_text: Came here for the Alaskan King Crab dinner with my family this week and it was amazing and super reasonably priced. They pre-order the crab once you confirm your reservation and show you the crab before bringing it into the kitchen to cook (it was alive and flailing). The crab was perfectly cooked into 4 dishes. The legs and claws were steamed with garlic, the body fried with salt/pepper/shallot/garlic, seafood fried rice was baked into the shell, and residual meat/juice was used to poach some yuchoy. Everything was perfectly cooked and tasted fresh and delicious. Service was amazing too. You have to drive through some shady areas of Vancouver, but definitely work the trip. Highly recommend and would go back in a heartbeat.

reviews.review_text: Prepare yourself for a wild ride because Pelican Restaurant in East Hastings is not your average dining establishment. If youre an adventurous foodie seeking new taste experiences, this place is a hidden gem that deserves your attention. However, if youre looking for a visually stunning, Instagram-worthy ambiance, well, lets just say you wont find it here. Upon entering Pelican Restaurant, you may be underwhelmed by its lackluster decor. But remember, its the taste that matters, right? And boy, oh boy, did Pelican deliver in that department. Every dish we devoured was an explosion of flavors that made our taste buds dance happily. We decided to visit Pelican for brunch, and it turned out to be an epic choice. Who needs pancakes and eggs benedict when you can have a unique culinary experience like no other? We knew we were in for something extraordinary when they opened their doors at 10 am. The menu at Pelican is a delightful mishmash of creative concoctions that will challenge your preconceived notions of what a brunch should be. Expect the unexpected as you peruse through their intriguing selection. From out-of-this-world flavor combinations to random ingredients, Pelican dares to push the boundaries of culinary norms. As we devoured each plate, we couldnt help but appreciate the boldness and creativity that went into the dishes. Pelican Restaurant is a playground for innovative flavors and unexpected pairings. Sure, the decor might not be Insta-worthy, and the ambiance lacks pizzazz, but who needs that when the food is this extraordinary? Pelican is a haven for true food enthusiasts who are willing to step outside their comfort zones and embrace the weird and wonderful. So, if youre a true gastronomic adventurer seeking a new experience of taste, make your way to Pelican Restaurant in East Hastings. Come with an open mind, and an empty stomach, and prepare to have your taste buds blown away. Trust me, its a brunch you wont soon forget.

reviews.review_text: Still my familys go-to place. Weve had dim sum regularly, simple dinners to a $1000 dinner here. It is consistently good food Chinese food. Dim sum is simple here, not too many creative/different dishes, just the good old favorites. Serving size isnt Western-Lake-size (also really enjoy that restaurant) but quite fair for the price. Service is good, tea is filled timely, never felt rushed to eat. I dont understand complaints about sequential food delivery; when the kitchen finishes the dish, the servers get it out ASAP. Would you really rather have a dish sit under a heat lamp while waiting for another dish to be completed? Ambience is just a typical Chinese restaurant. Chairs show wear and washroom needs a renovation but its not the worst...
We thoroughly enjoyed our dining experience at this establishment. Excellent and authentic cuisine!

reviews.review_text: Used to go here all the time for dim sum.  Always knew it was good because my  chinese grandma goes to ALL the chinese places and weeds out the bad quality/deal places before taking me somewhere and this is a place wed always come back to if in the area.  Now that the pandemic is full bore and there is no in person dining I went and ordered dinner food for the first time and it was SO GOOD.  I dont even like sweet and sour pork but everyone said it was the best they ever had.  Everything was incredibly tasty and well done. The place doesnt look like much from the outside but those who know, know that this is one of the best places for chinese in Van.

reviews.review_text: I come here with my in-laws and husbands grandparents for Dim Sum because they are regular customers. We get VIP treatment, they know what we like to order and always get some of our dishes started before we get seated. Service is great! Staff is friendly and attentive. Highly recommend their cha sui bao and beef parsley congee.

Best Chinese food ever!! The waiters speak very little english. But they are still very accommodating. Based on food alone, this is the best place for chinese food. So tender, tasty, and perfect. I orderes the house special chow mein which was filled with big split prawns and white crab meat and large scallops. As well as the sweet and sour pork which was done perfectly and not chewy. As well as veggie mix that had my two year old asking for more broccoli. Absolutely love this place and definitely going back.
